A UNT Dallas business student was released from Medical City Plano this week after beating COVID-19, according to published reports.
Christopher Marshall, 37, of Dallas, told KXAS-TV (NBC5) that he first started feeling ill in mid-March.
His health declined, he went into a coma and was flown to Medical City Plano.
“He was discharged after 12 days on a ventilator, six days on ECMO and a total of 17 days at Medical City Plano,” the caption on a Medical City Plano YouTube video states.
As of April 17, the city of Plano reported having 151 confirmed cases of the coronavirus and one death.